{"text": " I have a question, how does this sewage water become safe enough to drink? Because this guy is about to drink it. So when your waste water goes down the drain, it first goes into a facility where they filter out large debris. Then into giant tanks like these, where smaller particles settle to the bottom. But the most important part is when the water is sent through tubes that look like this. Here, powerful engines push water through a membrane that's so fine, the bacteria, and darts, and salts, and even tiny viruses get filtered out. Some treatment plants even use UV light and special chemical reactions. And the result is incredibly pure water. There's so many smart ways to get people clean drinking water, and team water is trying to get two million people clean drinking water for decades. I'm doing a one-hour call with one donor. Go donate so we can talk. There's a link in my description. It's going to be a team water. One dollar is one year for drinking water, so we need to use it.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 4.64, "text": " I have a question, how does this sewage water become safe enough to drink?", "tokens": [50364, 286, 362, 257, 1168, 11, 577, 775, 341, 15472, 609, 1281, 1813, 3273, 1547, 281, 2822, 30, 50596], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17008532010591948, "compression_ratio": 1.7331189710610932, "no_speech_prob": 0.0021722072269767523}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 4.64, "end": 6.24, "text": " Because this guy is about to drink it.", "tokens": [50596, 1436, 341, 2146, 307, 466, 281, 2822, 309, 13, 50676], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17008532010591948, "compression_ratio": 1.7331189710610932, "no_speech_prob": 0.0021722072269767523}, {"id": 2, "seek": 0, "start": 6.24, "end": 11.120000000000001, "text": " So when your waste water goes down the drain, it first goes into a facility where they filter out large debris.", "tokens": [50676, 407, 562, 428, 5964, 1281, 1709, 760, 264, 12339, 11, 309, 700, 1